vativeusa.org/ ''The Conservative Caucus'']\n# {{note|enr}} [http://enr.construction.com/advertise/aboutUs/125enrHistory/990222.asp ''Huge Panama Canal Is Carved Out of the Jungle''], from Engineering News-Record\n# {{note|acphistory}} [http://www.pancanal.com/eng/history/history/ ''A History of the Panama Canal''], from the Panama Canal Authority\n# {{note|plaque}} [http://www.czbrats.com/Builders/plaque.htm ''The Case Of The Traveling Plaque''], about the plaque dedicated to Colonel David du Bose Gaillard\n# {{note|panadmin}} [http://www.azstarnet.com/allheadlines/153038 Panama delivers a lesson to isolationists ''by Andr\u00e9s Oppenheimer'']\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n\n{{Refbegin}}\n* Collin, Richard H. ''Theodore Roosevelt's Caribbean: The Panama Canal, the Monroe Doctrine, & the Latin American Context'' (Louisiana State U. Press, 1990), 520pp \n*Greene, Julie. (2009). ''The Canal Builders: Making America's Empire at the Panama Canal''. New York: The Penguin Press. {{ISBN|978-1-59420-201-8}} \n* Lafeber,  Walter. ''The Panama Canal: The Crisis in Historical Perspective'' (3rd ed. 1990), the standard scholarly account of diplomacy\n* Mellander, Gustavo A. (1971) ''The United States in Panamanian Politics: The Intriguing Formative Years''. Danville, Ill.: Interstate Publishers, OCLC 138568\n* Mellander, Gustavo A., Mellander, Nelly, \"Charles Edward Magoon: The Panama Years.\"  R\u00edo Piedras, Puerto Rico: Editorial Plaza Mayor. {{ISBN|1-56328-155-4}}. OCLC 42970390. (1999)\n*[[David McCullough|McCullough, David]]. (1977). ''[[The Path Between the Seas: The Creation of the Panama Canal, 1870-1914]]''. New York: Simon & Schuster. {{ISBN|0-671-22563-4}}\n* Parker, Matthew. (2008).''Panama Fever: The Epic Story of One of the Greatest Human Achievements of All Time--The Building of the Panama Canal.''  Doubleday. {{ISBN|978-0385515344}} \n* Smith,  Gaddis. ''Morality Reason, and Power: American Diplomacy in the Carter Years'' (1986) pp 