an: ''Masters and Servants on the Cape Eastern Frontier, 1760\u20131803''. (Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, 1999)\n* Raven-Hart, Rowland (ed.): ''Cape Good Hope, 1652\u20131702: The First Fifty Years of Dutch Colonisation as Seen by Callers'' [2 vols]. (Cape Town: A.A.Balkema, 1971)\n* Schoeman, Karel: ''Early Slavery at the Cape of Good Hope, 1652\u20131717''. (Pretoria: Protea Book House, 2007)\n* Schoeman, Karel: ''Portrait of a Slave Society: The Cape of Good Hope, 1717\u20131795''. (Pretoria: Protea Boekhuis, 2012)\n* Shell, Robert: ''Children of Bondage: A Social History of the Slave Society at the Cape of Good Hope, 1652\u20131838''. (Hanover, Conn.; Wesleya University Press, 1994)\n* Singh, Daleep: ''From Dutch South Africa to Republic of South Africa, 1652-1994. The Story of Three and a Half Centuries of Imperialism''. (New Delhi: Allied Publishers, 2010)\n* [[Dan Sleigh|Sleigh, Dan]]: ''Die Buiteposte: VOC-buiteposte onder Kaapse Bestuur, 1652-1795''. (Pretoria: HAUM, 1993)\n* Stapleton, Timothy J.: ''A Military History of South Africa: From the [[Khoikhoi\u2013Dutch Wars|Dutch-Khoi Wars]] to the End of Apartheid''. (Santa Barbara, CA.: Praeger, 2010)\n* Terreblanche, Sampie: ''A History of Inequality in South Africa, 1652\u20132002''. (Pietermaritzburg: University of Natal Press, 2002)\n* Theal, George McCall: ''History of South Africa under the Administration of the Dutch East India Company, 1652 to 1795''. Nabu Press, 2010, 474pp\n* Theal, George McCall: ''History of the Boers in South Africa; Or, the Wanderings and Wars of the Emigrant Farmers from Their Leaving the Cape Colony to the Acknowledgment of Their Independence by Great Britain''. (Greenwood Press, 1970, {{ISBN|0-8371-1661-9}})\n* Twidle, Hedley (2013). ''Writing the Company: From VOC Daghregister to Sleigh's Eilande'', South African Historical Journal 65(1) (2013): 125\u201352.\n* [[Francois Valentijn|Valentijn, Francois]]: ''Description of the Cape of Good Hope with Matters Concerning It''. (Amsterdam, 1726). [Edited and annotated by Prof. P. Serton, Maj. B. Raven-Hart, Dr. W. J. de Kock.]\n* Van der Merwe, P. J. : ''The Migrant Farmer in the History of the Cape Colony, 1657\u20131842''. Translated from the Dutch by Roger B. Beck. (Athens, Ohio: Ohio University Press, 1995)\n* Van Duin, Pieter; Ross, Robert: ''The Economy of the Cape Colony in the Eighteenth Century''. (Leiden: Centre for the History of European Expansion, 1987, pp. viii + 166)\n* [[Jan van Riebeeck|Van Riebeeck, Jan]]: ''1652\u20131662, Daghregister gehouden by den oppercoopman Jan Anthonisz van Riebeeck''. In Bosman, D.B. & B. Thorn (eds). ''Daghregister Gehouden by den Oppercoopman Jan Anthonisz van Riebeeck'', 3 vols. [Treated as a sequence of eleven manuscripts]. (Cape Town: Balkema, 1952\u20131957)\n* Verstegen, M.: ''De Indische Zeeherberg, De stichting van Zuid-Afrika door de VOC''. (Zaltbommel, 2001)\n* Viljoen, Russel: ''Jan Paerl: A Khoikhoi in Cape Colonial Society, 1761\u20131851''. (Boston, MA: Brill, 2006, pp. xviii + 213)\n* Viljoen, Russel S. (1995). \u201cDisease and Society: VOC Cape Town, Its People, and the Smallpox Epidemics of 1713, 1755, and 1767,\u201d Kleio 27\n* Welch, Sidney: ''Portuguese and Dutch in South Africa, 1641\u20131806''. (Cape Town: Juta Press, 1951)\n* [[Nigel Worden|Worden, Nigel]]: ''Slavery in Dutch South Africa''. (Cambridge University Press, 1985, pp. xiii + 207)\n* Worden, Nigel; van Heyningen, Elizabeth; Bickford-Smith, Vivian: ''Cape Town: The Making of a City''. (Cape Town: David Philip, 1998)\n* Worden, Nigel; Groenewald, G. (eds.): ''Trials of Slavery: Selected Documents Concerning Slaves from the Criminal Records of the Council of Justice at the Cape of Good Hope, 1705\u20131794''. (Cape Town: Van Riebeeck Society for the Publication of South African Historical Documents, 2005)\n* Worden, Nigel: ''Contingent Lives: Social Identity and Material Culture in the VOC World''. (Rondeboch: Historical Studies Department, University of Cape Town and ABC Press, 2007, pp. vi + 612)\n* Worden, Nigel (ed.): ''Cape Town between East and West: Social Identities in a Dutch Colonial Town''. (Hilversum: Verloren, 2012, pp. xxii + 264)\n* Worden, Nigel (2007). ''VOC Cape Town as an Indian Ocean Port'', in Himanshu Prabha Ray and Edward A. Alpers (eds.), Cross Currents and Community Networks: The History of the Indian Ocean World (Oxford: Oxford University Press, 2007), pp.&nbsp;142\u201362\n* Worden, Nigel (2007). ''New Approaches to VOC History in South Africa''. South African Historical Journal 59 (2007)(1):3-18\n* Worden, Nigel (2010). ''After Race and Class: Recent Trends in the Historiography of Early Colonial Cape Society'', South African Historical Journal, 62 (2010)\n* Worden, Nigel (2014). ''Cape Slaves in the Paper Empire of the VOC''. (Kronos 40(1):23-44)\n* Worden, Nigel (2016). ''Indian Ocean Slaves in Cape Town, 1695\u20131807'', journal of Southern African Studies, 42 (2016): 389-408\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.saha.org.za/collections.htm South African History Archive]\n*[http://cdm164001.cdmhost.com/krogh/item_viewer.php?CISOROOT=/p164001coll21&CISOPTR=224&CISOBOX=1&REC=3 Democratic Development in South Africa] from the [http://cdm164001.cdmhost.com/krogh/ Dean Peter Krogh Foreign Affairs Digital Archives]\n*[http://www.sahistory.org.za South African History Online]\n*[http://www.mediaclub.co.za/culture/35-culture/culture-bg/104-history The History of South Africa] Brand South Africa. Accessed 24 November 2017.\n*[http://www.gov.za South Africa Government Online]. Accessed 20 February 2005.\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070621043856/http://www.villagelife.co.za/NewFiles/15_hromnik.pdf Dr Cyril Hromn\u00edk on research into ancient history of Africa] \u2013 an article written by Mar\u00e9 Mouton.\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20050414045450/http://www.afrikanerbond.org.za/Dokideal.pdf ''Bearer of an Ideal''] \u2013 a public-release document of the Afrikanerbond (formerly ''Afrikaner Broederbond''): think-tank which influenced policies of separate development in South Africa\n*[http://www.unhchr.ch/html/menu3/b/11.htm Full text of the UN convention]\n*[https://www.npr.org/news/specials/mandela/ South Africa, 10 years later] from US [[National Public Radio]]\n* {{cite web |work=LibGuides |title= History: Useful links |url=http://libguides.ukzn.ac.za/content.php?pid=470272&sid=3850521 |publisher=[[University of KwaZulu-Natal]] Libraries }}\n* {{cite web |url=http://www.archivalplatform.org/registry/ |title=Registry |work=[[Archivalplatform.org]] |location=Rondebosch |access-date=5 October 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171005151526/http://www.archivalplatform.org/registry/ |archive-date=5 October 2017 |url-status=dead }} (Directory of South African archival and memory institutions and organisations)\n\n{{Navboxes\n|list =\n{{South Africa topics}}\n{{South Africa year nav}}\n{{History of Africa}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:History Of South Africa}}\n[[Category:History of South Africa| ]]\n", "name_user": "Wbm1058", "label": "safe", "comment": "fix miscapitalization (viaWP:JWB)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History_of_South_Africa"}
{"title_page": "Brent Urban", "text_new": "{{short description|Canadian-born American football defensive end}}\n{{Use Canadian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox NFL biography\n| name                = Brent Urban\n| image               = Brent Urban 2019 10-13.jpg\n| image_size          = \n| alt                 = \n| caption             = Urban with the Tennessee Titans in 2019\n| current_team        = Chicago Bears\n| number              = 92\n| position            = [[Defensive end]]\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1991|5|5}}\n| birth_place         = [[Mississauga]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| height_ft           = 6\n| height_in           = 7\n| weight_lbs          = 295\n| high_school         = [[Lorne Park Secondary School|Mississauga (ON) Lorne Park]]\n| college             = [[Virginia Cavaliers football|Virginia]]\n| draftyear           = 2014\n| draftround          = 4\n| draftpick           = 134\n| cfldraftyear        = 2013\n| cfldraftround       = 2\n| cfldraftpick        = 15\n| pastteams           = \n* [[Baltimore Ravens]] ({{NFL Year|2014}}\u2013{{NFL Year|2018}})\n* [[Tennessee Titans]] ({{NFL Year|2019}})\n* [[Chicago Bears]] ({{NFL Year|2019}}\u2013present)\n| status              = Active\n| highlights          = \n* Honorable Mention All-[[Atlantic Coast Conference|ACC]] (2013)\n| statleague          = NFL\n| statseason          = 2019\n| statlabel1          = [[Tackle (football move)|Total tackles]]\n| statvalue1          = 68\n| statlabel2          = [[Quarterback sack|Sacks]]\n| statvalue2          = 3.5\n| statlabel3          = [[Fumble|Forced fumbles]]\n| statvalue3          = 0\n| statlabel4          = [[Fumble|Fumble recoveries]]\n| statvalue4          = 0\n| statlabel5          = [[Interceptions]]\n| statvalue5          = 0\n|statlabel6=[[Pass deflected|Pass deflections]]\n|statvalue6=6\n| nflnew              = brenturban/2543765\n}}\n\n'''Brent Urban''' (born May 5, 1991) is a [[Canada|Canadian]] professional [[American football]] [[defensive end]] for the [[Chicago Bears]] of the [[National Football League]] (NFL). He was drafted by the [[Baltimore Ravens]] in the fourth round of the [[2014 NFL Draft]]. He played [[college football]] at [[Virginia Cavaliers football|Virginia]]. Urban is the 26th Canadian to ever be drafted to the NFL.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Mink|first1=Ryan|title=THE CAW: BRENT URBAN ALMOST PLAYED HOCKEY INSTEAD|url=http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/The-Caw-Brent-Urban-Almost-Played-Hockey-Instead/fa837bb0-5d46-4f77-be67-d57a99ce3c5c|website=baltimoreravens.com|accessdate=December 15, 2017|date=March 27, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171216034855/http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/The-Caw-Brent-Urban-Almost-Played-Hockey-Instead/fa837bb0-5d46-4f77-be67-d57a99ce3c5c|archive-date=December 16, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Canadians in Camp: Brent Urban|url=http://canada.nfl.com/2014/06/02/canadians-in-camp-3/|website=canada.nfl.com|accessdate=December 15, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140628102050/http://canada.nfl.com/2014/06/02/canadians-in-camp-3/|archive-date=June 28, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nHe has also played for the [[Tennessee Titans]].\n\n==High school career==\nUrban attended [[Lorne Park Secondary School]] in [[Mississauga|Mississauga, Ontario]], Canada, where he was a two-time ''[[Toronto Star]]'' All-Star selection for the [[high school football|football]] team. He had 16 tackles for loss, 10 sacks, and eight pass break-ups as a junior.\n\nHe was considered a two-star recruit by ''[[Rivals.com]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/footballrecruiting/football/recruiting/player-Brent-Urban-67851|title=Brent Urban|work=yahoo.com}}</ref>\n\nUrban grew up playing elite minor hockey in his youth playing for the Mississauga Reps and Vaughan Kings.  Among his minor hockey teammates growing up were [[Casey Cizikas]] of the New York Islanders, [[Ryan Ellis]] of the Nashville Predators and [[Ben Chiarot]] of the Winnipeg Jets.\n\n==College career==\nUrban attended the [[University of Virginia]] from 2009 to 2013. In [[2009 Virginia Cavaliers football team|2009]], he [[redshirt (college sports)|redshirted]] as a true freshman.  In [[2010 Virginia Cavaliers football team|2010]], he appeared in three games but did not record any statistics. In [[2011 Virginia Cavaliers football team|2011]], he appeared in all 13 games, recording 15 tackles, including 2.5 for loss. In [[2012 Virginia Cavaliers football team|2012]], he started all 12 games for the Cavaliers, totalling 20 tackles, including 2.5 for loss, two sacks, one forced fumble and recovered a fumble returning it 16 yards for a touchdown against [[Virginia Tech Hokies football|Virginia Tech]]. In [[2013 Virginia Cavaliers football team|2013]], he started eight games before missing the last four due to injury.  He recorded 40 tackles, including 11.5 for loss, one sack, and led the nation's defensive linemen with nine passes broken up despite missing four games.\n\n==Professional career==\n\n===Hamilton Tiger Cats===\nUrban was selected by the [[Hamilton Tiger-Cats]] in the second round, 15th overall, of the [[2013 CFL Draft]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ticats.ca/article/eight-picks-2013-draft|title=Eight Picks Made In 2013 Draft|work=ticats.ca}}</ref> The club would hold his rights if/when he decides to play in the [[Canadian Football League]].\n\n===Baltimore Ravens===\n[[File:Brent Urban 2018 preseason.jpg|thumb|Brent Urban 2018 preseason]]\nUrban was drafted by the [[Baltimore Ravens]] in the fourth round (134th overall) of the [[2014 NFL Draft]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/sports/football/virginia-defensive-lineman-brent-urban-first-canadian-taken-in-nfl-draft/article18596469/|title=Virginia defensive lineman Brent Urban first Canadian taken in NFL draft|work=The Globe and Mail}}</ref> He sustained a torn [[Anterior cruciate ligament|ACL]] in training camp, where coach [[John Harbaugh]] announced that he would miss the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap2000000371970/article/baltimore-ravens-rookie-brent-urban-tears-acl|title=Baltimore Ravens rookie Brent Urban tears ACL|work=NFL.com}}</ref> He was placed on injured reserve on August 25, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/Ravens-Trim-Roster-Down-To-75/393025cc-1a69-4134-95a2-c2e561131580|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171117065055/http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/Ravens-Trim-Roster-Down-To-75/393025cc-1a69-4134-95a2-c2e561131580|url-status=dead|archive-date=November 17, 2017|title=Ravens Trim Roster Down To 75|work=BaltimoreRavens.com|date=August 25, 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn August 8, 2015, Urban tore his biceps muscle in training camp and was placed on injured reserve with the designation to return.<ref>{{cite web|title=Brent Urban Out 12-14 Weeks With Torn Biceps|url=http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/Brent-Urban-Out-12-14-Weeks-With-Torn-Biceps/268a266e-5f83-4c04-aca8-3275c9db1085|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170506065242/http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/Brent-Urban-Out-12-14-Weeks-With-Torn-Biceps/268a266e-5f83-4c04-aca8-3275c9db1085|url-status=dead|archive-date=May 6, 2017|author=Mink, Ryan|website=BaltimoreRavens.com|date=August 8, 2015|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref> He returned to practice on November 9 and was officially added to the active roster on November 25, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ravens DE Brent Urban Moved To Active Roster|url=http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/Ravens-DE-Brent-Urban-Moved-To-Active-Roster/798a41e6-8111-4872-a235-687ddf37aaf6|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170505062300/http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/Ravens-DE-Brent-Urban-Moved-To-Active-Roster/798a41e6-8111-4872-a235-687ddf37aaf6|url-status=dead|archive-date=May 5, 2017|author=Mink, Ryan|website=BaltimoreRavens.com|date=November 25, 2015|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref> In his first NFL game in Week 12 against the [[2015 Cleveland Browns season|Cleveland Browns]], Urban blocked a potential game-winning field goal as time expired, while teammate [[Will Hill]] recovered it and returned it for the game-winning touchdown.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2015/dec/01/kick-six-last-play-of-game-gives-ravens-stunning-win-over-browns|title=Kick six on last play of game gives Ravens stunning win over Browns|publisher=The Guardian|date=December 1, 2015|accessdate=December 1, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Urban played in all 16 games, recording 10 tackles and two passes defended.\n\nIn Week 3 of the 2017 season, Urban suffered a Lisfranc foot injury which required surgery.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ravens Defensive End Brent Urban Having Surgery After Lisfranc Foot Injury|url=http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/Ravens-Defensive-End-Brent-Urban-Having-Surgery-After-Lisfranc-Foot-Injury/cdf2d068-f812-4c19-b059-f72a1ec5cc42|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180118223352/http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/Ravens-Defensive-End-Brent-Urban-Having-Surgery-After-Lisfranc-Foot-Injury/cdf2d068-f812-4c19-b059-f72a1ec5cc42|url-status=dead|archive-date=January 18, 2018|author=Mink, Ryan|website=BaltimoreRavens.com|date=September 25, 2017}}</ref> He was placed on injured reserve on September 27, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ravens Sign Veteran Linebacker Jonathan Freeny|url=http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/Ravens-Sign-Veteran-Linebacker-Jonathan-Freeny/948f1823-e2e6-4c38-bee0-7355b4194c26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180119020207/http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/Ravens-Sign-Veteran-Linebacker-Jonathan-Freeny/948f1823-e2e6-4c38-bee0-7355b4194c26|url-status=dead|archive-date=January 19, 2018|author=Mink, Ryan|website=BaltimoreRavens.com|date=September 27, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn March 6, 2018, Urban signed a one-year contract extension with the Ravens for $2.35 million.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ravens sign Brent Urban to one-year contract|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000919769/article/ravens-sign-brent-urban-to-oneyear-contract|author=Shook, Nick|website=NFL.com|date=March 6, 2018}}</ref> He started all 16 games in 2018, recording 27 combined tackles, 0.5 sacks, and two passes defensed.\n\n===Tennessee Titans===\nOn April 26, 2019, Urban signed with the [[Tennessee Titans]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Titans Agree To Terms With Former Ravens DL Brent Urban|url=https://www.titansonline.com/news/titans-agree-to-terms-with-former-ravens-dl-brent-urban|author=Wyatt, Jim|website=TitansOnline.com|date=April 26, 2019}}</ref> He was released on October 19, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|title=Titans Add First-Round Pick Jeffery Simmons - and OLB Derick Roberson - to 53-Man Roster For Sunday\u2019s Game vs. Chargers|url=https://www.titansonline.com/news/titans-add-first-round-pick-jeffery-simmons-and-olb-derick-roberson-to-53-man-ro|author=Wyatt, Jim|website=TitansOnline.com|date=October 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Chicago Bears=== \nOn October 21, 2019, two days after being released by the Titans, Urban signed with the [[Chicago Bears]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Roster moves: Bears sign Urban, waive Harris|url=https://www.chicagobears.com/news/roster-moves-bears-sign-urban-waive-harris|author=Mayer, Larry|website=ChicagoBears.com|date=October 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\nUrban re-signed with the Bears on March 26, 2020.<ref>{{cite news |author=Mayer, Larry |title=Bears make seven free-agent signings official |url=https://www.chicagobears.com/news/bears-make-seven-free-agent-signings-official |website=ChicagoBears.com |date=March 26, 2020 |accessdate=March 26, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.virginiasports.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/brent_urban_799954.html Virginia Cavaliers bio]\n\n{{Ravens2014DraftPicks}}\n{{Chicago Bears roster navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Urban, Brent}}\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Mississauga]]\n[[Category:Canadian players of American football]]\n[[Category:American football defensive tackles]]\n[[Category:American football defensive ends]]\n[[Category:Virginia Cavaliers football players]]\n[[Category:Baltimore Ravens players]]\n[[Category:Tennessee Titans players]]\n[[Category:Chicago Bears players]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Canadian-born American football defensive end}}\n{{Use Canadian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox NFL biography\n| name                = Brent Urban\n| image               = Brent Urban 2019 10-13.jpg\n| image_size          = \n| alt                 = \n| caption             = Urban with the Tennessee Titans in 2019\n| current_team        = Chicago Bears\n| number              = 92\n| position            = [[Defensive end]]\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1991|5|5}}\n| birth_place         = [[Mississauga]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| height_ft           = 6\n| height_in           = 7\n| weight_lbs          = 295\n| high_school         = [[Lorne Park Secondary School|Mississauga (ON) Lorne Park]]\n| college             = [[Virginia Cavaliers football|Virginia]]\n| draftyear           = 2014\n| draftround          = 4\n| draftpick           = 134\n| cfldraftyear        = 2013\n| cfldraftround       = 2\n| cfldraftpick        = 15\n| pastteams           = \n* [[Baltimore Ravens]] ({{NFL Year|2014}}\u2013{{NFL Year|2018}})\n* [[Tennessee Titans]] ({{NFL Year|2019}})\n* [[Chicago Bears]] ({{NFL Year|2019}}\u2013present)\n| status              = Active\n| highlights          = \n* Honorable Mention All-[[Atlantic Coast Conference|ACC]] (2013)\n| statleague          = NFL\n| statseason          = 2019\n| statlabel1          = [[Tackle (football move)|Total tackles]]\n| statvalue1          = 68\n| statlabel2          = [[Quarterback sack|Sacks]]\n| statvalue2          = 3.5\n| statlabel3          = [[Fumble|Forced fumbles]]\n| statvalue3          = 0\n| statlabel4          = [[Fumble|Fumble recoveries]]\n| statvalue4          = 0\n| statlabel5          = [[Interceptions]]\n| statvalue5          = 0\n|statlabel6=[[Pass deflected|Pass deflections]]\n|statvalue6=6\n| nflnew              = brenturban/2543765\n}}\n\n'''Brent Urban''' (born May 5, 1991) is a [[Canada|Canadian]] professional [[American football]] [[defensive end]] for the [[Chicago Bears]] of the [[National Football League]] (NFL). He was drafted by the [[Baltimore Ravens]] in the fourth round of the [[2014 NFL Draft]]. He played [[college football]] at [[Virginia Cavaliers football|Virginia]]. Urban is the 26th Canadian to ever be drafted to the NFL.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Mink|first1=Ryan|title=THE CAW: BRENT URBAN ALMOST PLAYED HOCKEY INSTEAD|url=http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/The-Caw-Brent-Urban-Almost-Played-Hockey-Instead/fa837bb0-5d46-4f77-be67-d57a99ce3c5c|website=baltimoreravens.com|accessdate=December 15, 2017|date=March 27, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171216034855/http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/The-Caw-Brent-Urban-Almost-Played-Hockey-Instead/fa837bb0-5d46-4f77-be67-d57a99ce3c5c|archive-date=December 16, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Canadians in Camp: Brent Urban|url=http://canada.nfl.com/2014/06/02/canadians-in-camp-3/|website=canada.nfl.com|accessdate=December 15, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140628102050/http://canada.nfl.com/2014/06/02/canadians-in-camp-3/|archive-date=June 28, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nHe has also played for the [[Tennessee Titans]].\n\n==High school career==\nUrban attended [[Lorne Park Secondary School]] in [[Mississauga|Mississauga, Ontario]], Canada, where he was a two-time ''[[Toronto Star]]'' All-Star selection for the [[high school football|football]] team. He had 16 tackles for loss, 10 sacks, and eight pass break-ups as a junior.\n\nHe was considered a two-star recruit by ''[[Rivals.com]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/footballrecruiting/football/recruiting/player-Brent-Urban-67851|title=Brent Urban|work=yahoo.com}}</ref>\n\n==College career==\nUrban attended the [[University of Virginia]] from 2009 to 2013. In [[2009 Virginia Cavaliers football team|2009]], he [[redshirt (college sports)|redshirted]] as a true freshman.  In [[2010 Virginia Cavaliers football team|2010]], he appeared in three games but did not record any statistics. In [[2011 Virginia Cavaliers football team|2011]], he appeared in all 13 games, recording 15 tackles, including 2.5 for loss. In [[2012 Virginia Cavaliers football team|2012]], he started all 12 games for the Cavaliers, totalling 20 tackles, including 2.5 for loss, two sacks, one forced fumble and recovered a fumble returning it 16 yards for a touchdown against [[Virginia Tech Hokies football|Virginia Tech]]. In [[2013 Virginia Cavaliers football team|2013]], he started eight games before missing the last four due to injury.  He recorded 40 tackles, including 11.5 for loss, one sack, and led the nation's defensive linemen with nine passes broken up despite missing four games.\n\n==Professional career==\n\n===Hamilton Tiger Cats===\nUrban was selected by the [[Hamilton Tiger-Cats]] in the second round, 15th overall, of the [[2013 CFL Draft]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ticats.ca/article/eight-picks-2013-draft|title=Eight Picks Made In 2013 Draft|work=ticats.ca}}</ref> The club would hold his rights if/when he decides to play in the [[Canadian Football League]].\n\n===Baltimore Ravens===\n[[File:Brent Urban 2018 preseason.jpg|thumb|Brent Urban 2018 preseason]]\nUrban was drafted by the [[Baltimore Ravens]] in the fourth round (134th overall) of the [[2014 NFL Draft]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/sports/football/virginia-defensive-lineman-brent-urban-first-canadian-taken-in-nfl-draft/article18596469/|title=Virginia defensive lineman Brent Urban first Canadian taken in NFL draft|work=The Globe and Mail}}</ref> He sustained a torn [[Anterior cruciate ligament|ACL]] in training camp, where coach [[John Harbaugh]] announced that he would miss the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap2000000371970/article/baltimore-ravens-rookie-brent-urban-tears-acl|title=Baltimore Ravens rookie Brent Urban tears ACL|work=NFL.com}}</ref> He was placed on injured reserve on August 25, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/Ravens-Trim-Roster-Down-To-75/393025cc-1a69-4134-95a2-c2e561131580|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171117065055/http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/Ravens-Trim-Roster-Down-To-75/393025cc-1a69-4134-95a2-c2e561131580|url-status=dead|archive-date=November 17, 2017|title=Ravens Trim Roster Down To 75|work=BaltimoreRavens.com|date=August 25, 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn August 8, 2015, Urban tore his biceps muscle in training camp and was placed on injured reserve with the designation to return.<ref>{{cite web|title=Brent Urban Out 12-14 Weeks With Torn Biceps|url=http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/Brent-Urban-Out-12-14-Weeks-With-Torn-Biceps/268a266e-5f83-4c04-aca8-3275c9db1085|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170506065242/http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/Brent-Urban-Out-12-14-Weeks-With-Torn-Biceps/268a266e-5f83-4c04-aca8-3275c9db1085|url-status=dead|archive-date=May 6, 2017|author=Mink, Ryan|website=BaltimoreRavens.com|date=August 8, 2015|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref> He returned to practice on November 9 and was officially added to the active roster on November 25, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ravens DE Brent Urban Moved To Active Roster|url=http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/Ravens-DE-Brent-Urban-Moved-To-Active-Roster/798a41e6-8111-4872-a235-687ddf37aaf6|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170505062300/http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/Ravens-DE-Brent-Urban-Moved-To-Active-Roster/798a41e6-8111-4872-a235-687ddf37aaf6|url-status=dead|archive-date=May 5, 2017|author=Mink, Ryan|website=BaltimoreRavens.com|date=November 25, 2015|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref> In his first NFL game in Week 12 against the [[2015 Cleveland Browns season|Cleveland Browns]], Urban blocked a potential game-winning field goal as time expired, while teammate [[Will Hill]] recovered it and returned it for the game-winning touchdown.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2015/dec/01/kick-six-last-play-of-game-gives-ravens-stunning-win-over-browns|title=Kick six on last play of game gives Ravens stunning win over Browns|publisher=The Guardian|date=December 1, 2015|accessdate=December 1, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Urban played in all 16 games, recording 10 tackles and two passes defended.\n\nIn Week 3 of the 2017 season, Urban suffered a Lisfranc foot injury which required surgery.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ravens Defensive End Brent Urban Having Surgery After Lisfranc Foot Injury|url=http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/Ravens-Defensive-End-Brent-Urban-Having-Surgery-After-Lisfranc-Foot-Injury/cdf2d068-f812-4c19-b059-f72a1ec5cc42|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180118223352/http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/Ravens-Defensive-End-Brent-Urban-Having-Surgery-After-Lisfranc-Foot-Injury/cdf2d068-f812-4c19-b059-f72a1ec5cc42|url-status=dead|archive-date=January 18, 2018|author=Mink, Ryan|website=BaltimoreRavens.com|date=September 25, 2017}}</ref> He was placed on injured reserve on September 27, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ravens Sign Veteran Linebacker Jonathan Freeny|url=http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/Ravens-Sign-Veteran-Linebacker-Jonathan-Freeny/948f1823-e2e6-4c38-bee0-7355b4194c26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180119020207/http://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/article-1/Ravens-Sign-Veteran-Linebacker-Jonathan-Freeny/948f1823-e2e6-4c38-bee0-7355b4194c26|url-status=dead|archive-date=January 19, 2018|author=Mink, Ryan|website=BaltimoreRavens.com|date=September 27, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn March 6, 2018, Urban signed a one-year contract extension with the Ravens for $2.35 million.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ravens sign Brent Urban to one-year contract|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000919769/article/ravens-sign-brent-urban-to-oneyear-contract|author=Shook, Nick|website=NFL.com|date=March 6, 2018}}</ref> He started all 16 games in 2018, recording 27 combined tackles, 0.5 sacks, and two passes defensed.\n\n===Tennessee Titans===\nOn April 26, 2019, Urban signed with the [[Tennessee Titans]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Titans Agree To Terms With Former Ravens DL Brent Urban|url=https://www.titansonline.com/news/titans-agree-to-terms-with-former-ravens-dl-brent-urban|author=Wyatt, Jim|website=TitansOnline.com|date=April 26, 2019}}</ref> He was released on October 19, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|title=Titans Add First-Round Pick Jeffery Simmons - and OLB Derick Roberson - to 53-Man Roster For Sunday\u2019s Game vs. Chargers|url=https://www.titansonline.com/news/titans-add-first-round-pick-jeffery-simmons-and-olb-derick-roberson-to-53-man-ro|author=Wyatt, Jim|website=TitansOnline.com|date=October 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Chicago Bears=== \nOn October 21, 2019, two days after being released by the Titans, Urban signed with the [[Chicago Bears]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Roster moves: Bears sign Urban, waive Harris|url=https://www.chicagobears.com/news/roster-moves-bears-sign-urban-waive-harris|author=Mayer, Larry|website=ChicagoBears.com|date=October 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\nUrban re-signed with the Bears on March 26, 2020.<ref>{{cite news |author=Mayer, Larry |title=Bears make seven free-agent signings official |url=https://www.chicagobears.com/news/bears-make-seven-free-agent-signings-official |website=ChicagoBears.com |date=March 26, 2020 |accessdate=March 26, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{